# Why this exists:
#
# @stratchai/strategy-spec@0.5.0 declares a peer-dep on @stratchai/indicators
# @^0.2.1 — but indicators has since shipped 0.3.x and 0.4.x with no
# breaking changes that affect strategy-spec. The peer range upstream is
# stale, not load-bearing. Until strategy-spec ships a peer-range bump,
# plain `npm install` fails with ERESOLVE on a clean checkout.
#
# legacy-peer-deps=true reverts to npm v6-style peer-dep handling, which
# warns rather than refusing. The runtime is verified working — see
# commit history for the dogfooding finds.
#
# Side effect: this disables strict peer-dep enforcement for ALL deps in
# this project, not just the known-broken one. The tradeoff is intentional
# for hackathon dev-experience (clone + npm install + npm run dev) over
# strict resolution. If a future dep adds a *real* conflict we'd want to
# catch, run `npm install --no-legacy-peer-deps` ad-hoc to surface it.
legacy-peer-deps=true
